    {
      "id": "8106efb8_13ae043c",
      "file_path": "certServiceClient/README.md",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 42,
      "message": "Container is supposed to run and stop, so it may be hard to exec into it. Accessing logs would be easier using console appender with: docker logs aaf-certservice-client. Other ways would be to copy the logs using docker cp (it can be used on stopped containers) or commiting the container to new image and running it with something like: docker run -it --entrypoint sh commited-image.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6044,
        "name": "Remigiusz Janeczek",
